05/06/2003
MADRID, Spain -- On Wednesday (4 June), Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul met with US Deputy State Secretary Marc Grossman while in Madrid attending the NATO Foreign Ministers' Spring Term Meetings. The two officials discussed US-Turkish relations. Gul confirmed that either he or Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan would visit Washington soon.
Also Wednesday in Madrid, Greek Foreign Minister George Papandreou and Gul discussed the Turkish violations of Greek airspace over the Aegean. Both officials expressed willingness to solve the recurring problem. (Anadolu Agency, NTV, ANA - 04/06/03)
